Description: The Holy Family meeting the Infant Baptist on their return from Egypt; after Titian; landscape with the Virgin seated underneath a tree and St John playing with the Christ Child in her lap; Joseph tending to the ass at left. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Hendrick van der Borcht the Younger
Published by: Hendrick van der Borcht the Younger
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / German engravings, etchings and woodcuts c.1400-1700 (Undescribed) (D+F)
Associated names: Representation of: St John the Baptist (Prodromos)
Acquisition notes: The 208 items in the 1950 purchase from the Liechtenstein collection consisted of Italian prints. They were views of Rome; prints after Titian; portraits of Roman Emperors; and various other prints after Venetian artists.
